{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":879,"text":"The first time I stood\nin the operating room"},{"time":2855,"text":"and watched a real surgery,"},{"time":4727,"text":"I had no idea what to expect."},{"time":7302,"text":"I was a college student in engineering."},{"time":9277,"text":"I thought it was going to be like on TV."},{"time":11477,"text":"Ominous music playing in the background,"},{"time":13382,"text":"beads of sweat pouring down the surgeon's face."},{"time":16381,"text":"But it wasn't like that at all."},{"time":18541,"text":"There was music playing on this day,"},{"time":20140,"text":"I think it was Madonna's greatest hits. (Laughter)"},{"time":22862,"text":"And there was plenty of conversation,"},{"time":24989,"text":"not just about the patient's heart rate,"},{"time":26989,"text":"but about sports and weekend plans."},{"time":29762,"text":"And since then, the more surgeries I watched,"},{"time":31698,"text":"the more I realized this is how it is."},{"time":33525,"text":"In some weird way, it's just\nanother day at the office."},{"time":36278,"text":"But every so often"},{"time":38183,"text":"the music gets turned down,"},{"time":40281,"text":"everyone stops talking,"},{"time":41711,"text":"and stares at exactly the same thing."},{"time":44695,"text":"And that's when you know\nthat something absolutely critical"},{"time":46855,"text":"and dangerous is happening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49295,"text":"The first time I saw that"},{"time":50311,"text":"I was watching a type of surgery"},{"time":51543,"text":"called laparoscopic surgery"},{"time":53832,"text":"And for those of you who are unfamiliar,"},{"time":56390,"text":"laparoscopic surgery, instead of the large"},{"time":58783,"text":"open incision you might\nbe used to with surgery,"},{"time":61277,"text":"a laparoscopic surgery\nis where the surgeon creates"},{"time":63485,"text":"these three or more small\nincisions in the patient."},{"time":66502,"text":"And then inserts these long, thin instruments"},{"time":69368,"text":"and a camera,"},{"time":70482,"text":"and actually does the procedure inside the patient."},{"time":74333,"text":"This is great because there's\nmuch less risk of infection,"},{"time":76925,"text":"much less pain, shorter recovery time."},{"time":80085,"text":"But there is a trade-off,"},{"time":82677,"text":"because these incisions are created"},{"time":84461,"text":"with a long, pointed device"},{"time":86959,"text":"called a trocar."},{"time":88423,"text":"And the way the surgeon uses this device"},{"time":90617,"text":"is that he takes it"},{"time":92033,"text":"and he presses it into the abdomen"},{"time":94000,"text":"until it punctures through."},{"time":97255,"text":"And now the reason why \neveryone in the operating room"},{"time":100327,"text":"was staring at that device on that day"},{"time":102974,"text":"was because he had to be absolutely careful"},{"time":106205,"text":"not to plunge it through"},{"time":107672,"text":"and puncture it into the organs \nand blood vessels below."},{"time":111613,"text":"But this problem should seem \npretty familiar to all of you"},{"time":113452,"text":"because I'm pretty sure \nyou've seen it somewhere else."},{"time":116373,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":118165,"text":"Remember this?"},{"time":119821,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":123937,"text":"You knew that at any second"},{"time":125813,"text":"that straw was going to plunge through,"},{"time":127693,"text":"and you didn't know if it was \ngoing to go out the other side"},{"time":129278,"text":"and straight into your hand,"},{"time":130581,"text":"or if you were going to\nget juice everywhere,"},{"time":132277,"text":"but you were terrified. Right?"},{"time":135580,"text":"Every single time you did this,"},{"time":137556,"text":"you experienced the same\nfundamental physics"},{"time":140112,"text":"that I was watching in the operating room that day."},{"time":143192,"text":"And it turns out it really is a problem."},{"time":145738,"text":"In 2003, the FDA actually came out and said"},{"time":148530,"text":"that trocar incisions might \nbe the most dangerous step"},{"time":151907,"text":"in minimally invasive surgery."},{"time":153923,"text":"Again in 2009, we see a paper that says"},{"time":156363,"text":"that trocars account for over half"},{"time":158547,"text":"of all major complications in laparoscopic surgery."},{"time":162234,"text":"And, oh by the way,"},{"time":163376,"text":"this hasn't changed for 25 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166970,"text":"So when I got to graduate school,"},{"time":168500,"text":"this is what I wanted to work on."},{"time":170368,"text":"I was trying to explain to a friend of mine"},{"time":172176,"text":"what exactly I was spending my time doing,"},{"time":174291,"text":"and I said,"},{"time":176107,"text":"\"It's like when you're drilling through a wall"},{"time":178283,"text":"to hang something in your apartment."},{"time":181483,"text":"There's that moment when the drill\nfirst punctures through the wall"},{"time":185395,"text":"and there's this plunge. Right?"},{"time":191389,"text":"And he looked at me and he said,"},{"time":193430,"text":"\"You mean like when they drill \ninto people's brains?\""},{"time":196901,"text":"And I said, \"Excuse me?\" (Laughter)"},{"time":199233,"text":"And then I looked it up and they\ndo drill into people's brains."},{"time":202281,"text":"A lot of neurosurgical procedures"},{"time":204345,"text":"actually start with a drill\nincision through the skull."},{"time":208127,"text":"And if the surgeon isn't careful,"},{"time":209912,"text":"he can plunge directly into the brain."},{"time":213496,"text":"So this is the moment when I started thinking,"},{"time":215662,"text":"okay, cranial drilling, laparoscopic surgery,"},{"time":218970,"text":"why not other areas of medicine?"},{"time":220634,"text":"Because think about it, when was\nthe last time you went to the doctor"},{"time":222578,"text":"and you didn't get stuck with something? Right?"},{"time":225325,"text":"So the truth is"},{"time":226642,"text":"in medicine puncture is everywhere."},{"time":229194,"text":"And here are just a couple\nof the procedures that I've found"},{"time":231986,"text":"that involve some tissue puncture step."},{"time":235195,"text":"And if we take just three of them —"},{"time":237274,"text":"laparoscopic surgery, \nepidurals, and cranial drilling —"},{"time":241370,"text":"these procedures account \nfor over 30,000 complications"},{"time":245349,"text":"every year in this country alone."},{"time":248200,"text":"I call that a problem worth solving."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250915,"text":"So let's take a look at some of the devices"},{"time":253240,"text":"that are used in these types of procedures."},{"time":255744,"text":"I mentioned epidurals. This is an epidural needle."},{"time":258969,"text":"It's used to puncture through \nthe ligaments in the spine"},{"time":261286,"text":"and deliver anesthesia during childbirth."},{"time":263725,"text":"Here's a set of bone marrow biopsy tools."},{"time":266278,"text":"These are actually used\nto burrow into the bone"},{"time":268214,"text":"and collect bone marrow\nor sample bone lesions."},{"time":271714,"text":"Here's a bayonette from the Civil War."},{"time":273624,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":276640,"text":"If I had told you it was a \nmedical puncture device"},{"time":279233,"text":"you probably would have believed me."},{"time":281449,"text":"Because what's the difference?"},{"time":283642,"text":"So, the more I did this research"},{"time":285577,"text":"the more I thought there has to be"},{"time":287161,"text":"a better way to do this."},{"time":289190,"text":"And for me the key to this problem"},{"time":291609,"text":"is that all these different puncture devices"},{"time":294020,"text":"share a common set of fundamental physics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297822,"text":"So what are those physics?"},{"time":299374,"text":"Let's go back to drilling through a wall."},{"time":300966,"text":"So you're applying a force \non a drill towards the wall."},{"time":304598,"text":"And Newton says the wall\nis going to apply force back,"},{"time":307942,"text":"equal and opposite."},{"time":309207,"text":"So, as you drill through the wall,"},{"time":311170,"text":"those forces balance."},{"time":313100,"text":"But then there's that moment"},{"time":314641,"text":"when the drill first punctures\nthrough the other side of the wall,"},{"time":316777,"text":"and right at that moment \nthe wall can't push back anymore."},{"time":319633,"text":"But your brain hasn't reacted \nto that change in force."},{"time":323100,"text":"So for that millisecond,"},{"time":324161,"text":"or however long it takes you \nto react, you're still pushing,"},{"time":326793,"text":"and that unbalanced force \ncauses an acceleration,"},{"time":329337,"text":"and that is the plunge."},{"time":332449,"text":"But what if right at the moment of puncture"},{"time":336353,"text":"you could pull that tip back,"},{"time":337977,"text":"actually oppose the forward acceleration?"},{"time":340990,"text":"That's what I set out to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343127,"text":"So imagine you have a device"},{"time":344447,"text":"and it's got some kind of sharp tip \nto cut through tissue."},{"time":347647,"text":"What's the simplest way \nyou could pull that tip back?"},{"time":350860,"text":"I chose a spring."},{"time":352671,"text":"So when you extend that spring, \nyou extend that tip out"},{"time":355255,"text":"so it's ready to puncture tissue,"},{"time":357470,"text":"the spring wants to pull the tip back."},{"time":358910,"text":"How do you keep the tip in place"},{"time":360663,"text":"until the moment of puncture?"},{"time":363127,"text":"I used this mechanism."},{"time":365550,"text":"When the tip of the device\nis pressed against tissue,"},{"time":368111,"text":"the mechanism expands outwards \nand wedges in place against the wall."},{"time":371951,"text":"And the friction that's generated"},{"time":373655,"text":"locks it in place and prevents\nthe spring from retracting the tip."},{"time":376847,"text":"But right at the moment of puncture,"},{"time":378734,"text":"the tissue can't push back\non the tip anymore."},{"time":380798,"text":"So the mechanism unlocks \nand the spring retracts the tip."},{"time":383980,"text":"Let me show you that \nhappening in slow motion."},{"time":385630,"text":"This is about 2,000 frames a second,"},{"time":387278,"text":"and I'd like you to notice the tip"},{"time":389150,"text":"that's right there on the bottom, \nabout to puncture through tissue."},{"time":391778,"text":"And you'll see that \nright at the moment of puncture,"},{"time":396590,"text":"right there, the mechanism unlocks \nand retracts that tip back."},{"time":399892,"text":"I want to show it to you again, a little closer up."},{"time":402236,"text":"You're going to see the sharp bladed tip,"},{"time":404428,"text":"and right when it punctures \nthat rubber membrane"},{"time":406420,"text":"it's going to disappear\ninto this white blunt sheath."},{"time":410572,"text":"Right there."},{"time":412437,"text":"That happens within four 100ths \nof a second after puncture."},{"time":417101,"text":"And because this device is designed\nto address the physics of puncture"},{"time":420901,"text":"and not the specifics of cranial drilling"},{"time":422733,"text":"or laparoscopic surgery, \nor another procedure,"},{"time":424940,"text":"it's applicable across these\ndifferent medical disciplines"},{"time":427597,"text":"and across different length scales."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430628,"text":"But it didn't always look like this."},{"time":432741,"text":"This was my first prototype."},{"time":434926,"text":"Yes, those are popsicle sticks,"},{"time":437568,"text":"and there's a rubber band at the top."},{"time":439470,"text":"It took about 30 minutes to do this, but it worked."},{"time":442870,"text":"And it proved to me that my idea worked"},{"time":444566,"text":"and it justified the next couple\nyears of work on this project."},{"time":447958,"text":"I worked on this because"},{"time":449766,"text":"this problem really fascinated me."},{"time":451429,"text":"It kept me up at night."},{"time":453558,"text":"But I think it should fascinate you too,"},{"time":456540,"text":"because I said puncture is everywhere."},{"time":458442,"text":"That means at some point \nit's going to be your problem too."},{"time":462706,"text":"That first day in the operating room"},{"time":464266,"text":"I never expected to find myself \non the other end of a trocar."},{"time":467250,"text":"But last year, I got appendicitis \nwhen I was visiting Greece."},{"time":471140,"text":"So I was in the hospital in Athens,"},{"time":472970,"text":"and the surgeon was telling me"},{"time":474458,"text":"he was going to perform \na laparoscopic surgery."},{"time":476594,"text":"He was going to remove my appendix \nthrough these tiny incisions,"},{"time":479346,"text":"and he was talking about what\nI could expect for the recovery,"},{"time":482040,"text":"and what was going to happen."},{"time":483482,"text":"He said, \"Do you have any questions?\"\nAnd I said, \"Just one, doc."},{"time":485900,"text":"What kind of trocar do you use?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":489374,"text":"So my favorite quote \nabout laparoscopic surgery"},{"time":492879,"text":"comes from a Doctor H. C. Jacobaeus:"},{"time":495525,"text":"\"It is puncture itself that causes risk.\""},{"time":499189,"text":"That's my favorite quote \nbecause H.C. Jacobaeus"},{"time":502325,"text":"was the first person to ever perform \nlaparoscopic surgery on humans,"},{"time":506365,"text":"and he wrote that in 1912."},{"time":509797,"text":"This is a problem that's been injuring and\neven killing people for over 100 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":515581,"text":"So it's easy to think that for\nevery major problem out there"},{"time":517815,"text":"there's some team of experts \nworking around the clock to solve it."},{"time":521751,"text":"The truth is that's not always the case."},{"time":525100,"text":"We have to be better at finding those problems"},{"time":527545,"text":"and finding ways to solve them."},{"time":530313,"text":"So if you come across a problem that grabs you,"},{"time":533569,"text":"let it keep you up at night."},{"time":535450,"text":"Allow yourself to be fascinated,"},{"time":537593,"text":"because there are so many lives to save."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540505,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}